c7z4General Informationz0

Mail filters are also commonly known as "twit filters" or "spam killers".

Mail Filters are responsible for killing mail from users that you want to
ignore.  It is also possible to automatically suspend receipt of mails matching
a subject (the [S]ubject command).

   eg. :2if your Names list contains "Ray Akey@1:246/74", you would never receive mails through Fidonet from the developer of CNet Amiga. :(:0

       :2if your Names list contains "*@1:246/*.*", you would not get any mail from fidonet net 246 in zone 1.:0

       :2if your Names list contains "*@netrover.com", you would never receive mail from any user with an account at the ISP that the CNet developer gets his internet access.:0

       :2if your Names list contains "rakey@netrover.com", you would never receive internet mail from the developer of CNet Amiga.:0

       :2if your Subject list contained "*test*", you would never receive mails that have the word TEST anywhere in their subject/title.:0

       :2if your Subject list contained the word "spam", then you would never receive mails with a single word title of "spam".:0

Ask your sysop for more information if you are not sure about mail filters.
